# Screen titles

All **screen-level titles** (page headlines, greetings, auth headlines) use the same type style for consistency across home, setup, history, auth, and check-in.

- Use `Type.screenTitle` from `src/theme.ts` (`Slab.black` / Hepta Slab 900, `FontSize.display`, `letterSpacing: -1`).
- Do **not** use `Slab.bold` or `Slab.extraBold` for screen titles.
- Layer color, margin, and extra padding on top of `Type.screenTitle` as needed (e.g. mood `theme.ink`, descender padding on the home greeting).
- Section labels and in-card habit titles are separate — this rule is for the primary page headline only.

```tsx
// ❌ BAD — home greeting out of sync with setup/history
greeting: {
  fontFamily: Slab.bold,
  fontSize: FontSize.display,
}

// ✅ GOOD
import { Type } from '../src/theme';

greeting: {
  ...Type.screenTitle,
  // optional extras (margin, padding, overflow)
}
```
